definition.value: An organic cation that is 1,2,4,6-tetraoxohexahydropyrimidin-1-ium substituted by a cyclohex-1-en-1-yl group at position 5 and methyl groups at positions 3 and 5.

The intermediate in the biosynthesis of vitamin B12 from uroporphyrinogen III in which four methyl groups have been introduced at positions 2, 7, 17 and 20 of the tetrapyrrole framework, together with ring contraction of the framework forming a bond between C-1 and C-19, leaving C-20 as part of an acetyl group bonded to C-1.
An epoxide resulting from the formal epoxidation of the cyclic double bond of limonene.
A hydroxamic acid that is biphenyl-4-amine bearing N-hydroxy and N-acetyl substituents.
